## Terraform Module Source Pinning

Always pin external Terraform module sources to a full git commit SHA, not a tag or branch.

**Required pattern:**
```hcl
module "example" {
  source = "git::https://github.com/org/repo?ref=<full-commit-sha>"
```

**Rules:**
- `ref=` must be a 40-character hex commit SHA (e.g. `8c9aa471f83258ee1cad51c0cdfdb7f5f6a017cd`)
- Tags (`ref=v1.0.0`) and branches (`ref=main`) are not allowed
- A comment explaining what the pinned commit corresponds to is encouraged, e.g. `# module-name v1.2.3`
- This applies to all `git::` and `github.com/` module sources
